    "summary": "Since August 2017 I have been a passionate lecturer at AVANS University of Applied Sciences; until August 2019 in the School of International Studies (ASIS) and since then in AVANS Academy of Part-time Education as well as in the Academy of Integral Safety Sciences. \n\nThe dynamics of working with ambitious students inspires me. As a lecturer, coach, mentor or a sparring-partner I facilitate students on their \u2018journey\u2019 to become business professionals with a good understanding of Finance, who apply high ethical standards.\n\nDuring my previous career as a B2B specialist in the Financial Industry, I encountered the importance of a solid knowledge base on how Business Economics works. Not only for myself as a (commercial) account executive but also for managers and entrepreneurs themselves, in their preparations for finance and business decisions. \nAmong the topics covered in the strategic conversations I had with entrepreneurs were such things as Start Up\u2019s, Jump-Investments, MBO, M&A and also day-to-day International Business issues like International Cash and Trade Management, Currency Risk and Pricing. \n\nAdditionally, my Compliance experience touches upon integrity, culture, long term relationships, etc. It is about \u2018applied Ethics\u2019 and \u2018Social Entrepreneurship\u2019.\n\nMy professional experience and drive add value when I am guiding students during their internships or when I am mentoring projects or games, advising on business plans, etc. \nAll this results in top student evaluations and excellent feedback from colleagues.\n\nI love this profession!\n",
